==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Traditor
<hw>Trad"i*tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>tradere</ets>, <ets>traditum</ets>. See <er>Traitor</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>A deliverer; -- a name of infamy given to
Christians who delivered the Scriptures, or the goods of the church, to
their persecutors to save their lives.</def>
<rj><au>Milner.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

